# Program Counter Using Verilog HDL

## Overview

This project implements a 8-bit Program Counter (PC) using Verilog HDL. The Program Counter stores the address of the next instruction to be executed in a processor.

## Features

* 8-bit counter
* Asynchronous reset
* Increments on every positive clock edge
* Simple and beginner-friendly design

## Files

* design/program_counter.v
* testbench/tb_program_counter.v
* waveform/program_counter.vcd

## Working

When reset is asserted, the Program Counter becomes 0. After reset is deasserted, the counter increments by 1 on every positive clock edge.

## Applications

* CPU Design
* Instruction Fetch Unit
* Digital Systems
* VLSI and FPGA Projects

